  <eligibility>
    <study_pop>
      <textblock>
        Male subjects aged 18 years or older with histologically-confirmed prostate cancer, showing
        biochemical failure (defined as a rising PSA) following definitive therapy (surgery or
        radiation) and indicated to receive hormone therapy.
      </textblock>
    </study_pop>
    <sampling_method>Non-Probability Sample</sampling_method>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  18 years or older

          -  Received therapy of curative intent (surgery or radiotherapy)

          -  Have a rising PSA which has doubled from a nadir value.

          -  Histologically proven prostate cancer requiring androgen deprivation therapy for at
             least 12 months

          -  Written informed consent to participate in the trial.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Known hypersensitivity to Zoladex, Casodex, ar any component of these products

          -  Prior treatment with LHRH agonist or anti-androgens in the past 12 months

          -  Any concomitant condition that would make it undesirable, in the physician's opinion,
             for the subject to participate in the trial or would jeopardize compliance with the
             protocol.
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
